criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of systemic arterial hypertension, according to the VII Brazilian Guidelines
             for Hypertension;

          -  male;

          -  BMI <30;

          -  Age between 30 and 60 years;

          -  Minimum level of education: elementary school

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Present pathologies in the musculoskeletal and neurological systems, or incapacitating
             complaints in these systems;

          -  Diagnosis of psychiatric disorder;

          -  Being under medical treatment for insomnia or other psychiatric treatment.
